<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1934,2033]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,679]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1934,1960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Head</emphasis>
. Head 1.4 × as wide as long in anterior view (
<figureCitation box="[791,879,1934,1960]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
), 1.7 × as wide as in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1271,1360,1934,1960]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Eyes glabrous, slightly emarginated at level of antennal torulus (
<figureCitation box="[821,909,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Face 1.5 × as wide as long, punctate, setose, convex medially in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[528,617,2006,2032]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Clypeus 1.8 × as wide as high, smooth, sparsely setose, lower margin slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[353,442,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Malar suture present (
<figureCitation box="[716,805,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Malar space as long as basal width of mandible (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Mandible bidentate, upper and lower tooth equal in size (
<figureCitation box="[841,928,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Frons impressed medially, smooth, sparsely setose (
<figureCitation box="[235,323,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Ocellar area slightly elevated (
<figureCitation box="[687,808,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1C, E</figureCitation>
). Vertex and occiput smooth, setose (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1312,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina complete medio-dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[525,614,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). IOD 1.9 × as long as LOD, OOL 1.7 × as long as LOD, POL 2.0 × as long as LOD. Antenna with 30 flagellomeres (
<figureCitation box="[674,764,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). First flagellomere 5.7 × as long as wide and 1.8 × as long as second one. Terminal flagellomere 1.9 × as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,366,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Mesosoma 1.5 × as long as high (
<figureCitation box="[714,799,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum smooth, punctate laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1328,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Epomia raised into strong crest anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[541,627,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum 1.5 × as long as wide in dorsal view, moderately convex anteriorly, bordered by lateral carina, smooth, setose, interspace between puncture wide (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1238,437,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Scutellar sulcus shallowly impressed, smooth without crenulations (
<figureCitation box="[732,817,473,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Scutellum punctate, with lateral carina on its anterior 0.8, sparsely setose (
<figureCitation box="[390,477,509,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Epicnemial carina straight. Mesopleuron punctate except smooth posteriorly, with large excavation posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[487,611,545,571]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1D–E</figureCitation>
). Metapleuron moderately punctate, juxtacoxal carina complete, strongly broadened anteriorly and forming a lobe, pleural carina absent (
<figureCitation box="[914,1038,580,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-167@2.[151,1436,437,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, oblique view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854124/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1D–E</figureCitation>
). Propodeum punctate, setose with smooth area superomedia, anterior transverse carina absent laterally, posterior transverse carina complete, pair of oval pits ventrally bordered by carina present postero-medially (
<figureCitation box="[870,961,652,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854128" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6854128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854128/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" startId="4.[151,250,1972,1996]" targetBox="[166,1421,703,1949]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1972,2032]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,270,1972,1996]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">FIGURE 3</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ranjith &amp; Sheikh &amp; Priyadarsanan, 2022" authorityName="Ranjith &amp; Sheikh &amp; Priyadarsanan" authorityYear="2022" box="[283,454,1972,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lycorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sehgali" status="sp. nov.">
