</emphasis>
, holotype, female A) head &amp; fore leg, anterior view; B) hind legs, lateral view; C) ovipositor &amp; sheath, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[291,377,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Fore wing 2.9 × as long as wide. Pterostigma triangular. Vein 1cu-a slightly postfurcal. Vein 2rs-m 2.0 × as long as M between 2rs-m and 2m-cu. Hind wing vein CU+cu-a curved to the wing base, without vein CU. Vein RA with nine distal hamuli.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Legs</emphasis>
. Fore femur 4.5 × as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[659,749,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-272@4.[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) head &amp; fore leg, anterior view; B) hind legs, lateral view; C) ovipositor &amp; sheath, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854128/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Fore tibia 4.8 × as long as wide. Fore tarsus as long as fore tibia. Hind femur 6.0 × as long as wide and 0.8 × as long as hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[955,1043,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-272@4.[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) head &amp; fore leg, anterior view; B) hind legs, lateral view; C) ovipositor &amp; sheath, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854128/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Hind basitarsus 10.0 × as long as wide. Second hind tarsomere 3.6 × as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[744,832,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-272@4.[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) head &amp; fore leg, anterior view; B) hind legs, lateral view; C) ovipositor &amp; sheath, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854128/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Hind tarsus shorter than tibia. Tarsal claws strongly pectinate (
<figureCitation box="[267,395,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-272@4.[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) head &amp; fore leg, anterior view; B) hind legs, lateral view; C) ovipositor &amp; sheath, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854128/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Figs 3A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854130" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6854130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854130/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596" startId="5.[151,250,1936,1960]" targetBox="[151,1436,417,1912]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1936,1996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,270,1936,1960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">FIGURE 4</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kasparyan" authorityName="Kasparyan" authorityYear="2007" box="[283,599,1936,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lycorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">
<emphasis box="[283,481,1936,1960]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Lycorina ruficornis</emphasis>
Kasparyan
</taxonomicName>
, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) mesosoma, dorsal view; E) metasoma, dorsal view; F) wings.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854132" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6854132" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854132/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597" startId="6.[151,250,1700,1724]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1676]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1700,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,270,1700,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">FIGURE 5</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chao" authorityName="Chao" authorityYear="1980" box="[283,549,1700,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lycorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilonotae">
<emphasis box="[283,486,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Lycorina spilonotae</emphasis>
Chao
</taxonomicName>
, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) propodeum, dorsal view; F) metasoma, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1807,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1807,1833]" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Metasoma</emphasis>
. Metasomal tergites heavily sculptured (
<figureCitation box="[794,922,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Figs 2B–E</figureCitation>
). T1 0.9 × as long as maximum width, with smooth triangular area antero-medially bordered by posteriorly narrowing carinae, 1.6 × as long as T2 (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1387,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). T2 0.5 × as long as maximum width (
<figureCitation box="[526,613,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Median transverse area of T1 and an anterior area of T2–5 longitudinally punctate crenulate (
<figureCitation box="[370,498,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Figs 2C–D</figureCitation>
). Medial triangular area of T1–5, and a posterior area of T1–5 deeply punctate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Figs 2C–E</figureCitation>
). Medial triangular area of T5 distinctly bulged in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[922,1010,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). T6–8 entirely finely coriaceous (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-70@3.[151,1436,309,1804]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) propodeum, dorsal view; B) metasoma, lateral view; C) metasomal tergites 1–2, dorsal view; D) metasomal tergites 2–4, dorsal view; E) metasomal tergites 5–7, dorsal view; F) wings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854126/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheath 1.3 × as long as hind tibia. Ovipositor with dorsal nodus and ventral serrations (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1391,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-272@4.[166,1421,703,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lycorina sehgali sp. nov., holotype, female A) head &amp; fore leg, anterior view; B) hind legs, lateral view; C) ovipositor &amp; sheath, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854128/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="597">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854134" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6854134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854134/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="598" startId="7.[151,250,1700,1724]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1676]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1700,1761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1700,1724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">FIGURE 6</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Holmgren" authorityName="Holmgren" authorityYear="1859" box="[280,617,1700,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lycorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifera">
<emphasis box="[280,507,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">Lycorina triangulifera</emphasis>
Holmgren
</taxonomicName>
, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) propodeum, dorsal view; F) metasoma, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1806,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,283,1806,1832]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">Colour</emphasis>
. Body black except clypeus, mandible medially, maxillary and labial palps, outer eye margin, scutellum laterally and posterior half, metanotum medially, tegula, fore leg except anterior half of coxa, mid leg except dorsal part of coxa, T2–3 postero-medially, which are yellow; eye grey, hind trochanter, tibia apical 2/3, tarsus reddish brown, hind femur and ovipositor yellowish red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1806,2013]" box="[199,457,1951,1977]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1951,1977]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598">Male</emphasis>
. Same as female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,422,1986,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="598" type="biology_ecology">
